1. Write a test suite to test the correctness of PrimeSieve.

  * Calculate pi(x), pi2(x), ... and compare the results with known
    values
  * Do tests with different sieve sizes
  * Do memory extensive tests with a lot of allocation and
    deallocation
  * Test invalid input

  The test suite will be added to the console version of primesieve
  using the -test switch.

2. When C++0x is available use its new threading facilities and add
   Multi-thread support to the console version of primesieve.
   The threading facilities of C++0x will be portable and will not
   depend on additional libraries.

3. Use threads instead of processes in the GUI version of primesieve
   and change all "CPU cores" labels to "Threads".

4. Add support for arithmetic expression evaluation to the GUI
   version of primesieve.
